{
  "doc_id": "3986",
  "text": "In the present study, D2 activity and D2 mRNA were higher in NHOst cells than in SaOS-2 cells at the basal level and after forskolin stimulation. Lower D2 expression in a tumor cell line derived from osteosarcoma compared with that in normal osteoblast cells suggests that D2 expression may increase in differentiated osteoblast cells, because D2 expression in papillary thyroid carcinoma was lower than that in normal thyroid tissue [CITATION_1] . In earlier studies, 5Ј-deiodinase activity was not detected in UMR-106 rat osteoblastic osteosarcoma cells [CITATION_2] . D2 expression may be different among rat tissues and human tissues, because D2 is highly expressed in human thyroid gland, but is absent in rat thyroid gland [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
